  "prompt": "What is the best time to visit Kanniyakumari?",
  "response": "The best time to visit Kanniyakumari depends on your tolerance for heat and humidity. Here's a breakdown:\n\n*   **October to March (Winter):** This is widely considered the **best time** to visit.\n\n    *   **Weather:** Pleasant and comfortable, with temperatures ranging from 22\u00b0C to 30\u00b0C (72\u00b0F to 86\u00b0F).\n    *   **Ideal For:** Sightseeing, beach activities, and enjoying the sunrise and sunset. The weather is perfect for exploring all the attractions without being uncomfortable.\n    *   **Drawbacks:** This is peak season, so expect larger crowds and potentially higher prices for accommodation and transportation.\n\n*   **April to May (Summer):** This is the **least ideal time** to visit.\n\n    *   **Weather:** Hot and humid, with temperatures soaring to 35\u00b0C (95\u00b0F) or higher.\n    *   **Drawbacks:** The heat and humidity can be oppressive, making it difficult to enjoy outdoor activities. Sightseeing becomes challenging.\n    *   **Possible Benefits:** Fewer crowds and potentially lower prices.\n\n*   **June to September (Monsoon):**\n\n    *   **Weather:** Moderate rainfall.\n    *   **Benefits:** Lush greenery and a refreshing atmosphere after the rains. Reduced crowds compared to the peak season. Potentially lower prices.\n    *   **Drawbacks:** Heavy rains can disrupt travel plans and restrict outdoor activities. The sea can be rough, and certain attractions might be temporarily closed.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   **Best Time (Most Recommended):** October to March (Winter)\n*   **Avoid:** April to May (Summer)\n*   **Consider if you don't mind rain:** June to September (Monsoon)\n\nUltimately, the best time for *you* depends on your preferences and what you want to get out of your trip. If you prioritize comfortable weather and don't mind crowds, go during the winter. If you're on a budget and don't mind some rain, the monsoon season could be an option. If you can't stand heat, avoid the summer months.\n",
